}}\n{{Image label|x=390|y=590|scale=577/2060|text=[[Lanxi, Zhejiang|'''Lanxi<br>{{small|(city)}}''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1030|y=570|scale=577/2060|text=[[Yiwu|'''Yiwu<br>{{small|(city)}}''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1460|y=680|scale=577/2060|text=[[Dongyang|'''Dongyang<br>{{small|(city)}}''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1120|y=1110|scale=577/2060|text=[[Yongkang, Zhejiang|'''Yongkang<br>{{small|(city)}}''']]}}\n</div>\n|-\n! align=left          | Subdivision\n! align=left          | [[Simplified Chinese]]\n! align=left          | [[Pinyin]]\n|-\n| align=left | [[Wucheng District]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u5a7a\u57ce\u533a}}\n| align=right| W\u00f9ch\u00e9ng Q\u016b\n|-\n| align=left | [[Jindong District]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u91d1\u4e1c\u533a}}\n| align=right| J\u012bnd\u014dng Q\u016b\n|-\n| align=left | [[Lanxi, Zhejiang|Lanxi]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u5170\u6eaa\u5e02}}\n| align=right| L\u00e1nx\u012b Sh\u00ec\n|-\n| align=left | [[Yongkang, Zhejiang|Yongkang]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u6c38\u5eb7\u5e02}}\n| align=right| Y\u01d2ngk\u0101ng Sh\u00ec\n|-\n| align=left | [[Yiwu]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u4e49\u4e4c\u5e02}}\n| align=right| Y\u00ecw\u016b Sh\u00ec\n|-\n| align=left | [[Dongyang]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u4e1c\u9633\u5e02}}\n| align=right| D\u014dngy\u00e1ng Sh\u00ec\n|-\n| align=left | [[Wuyi County, Jinhua|Wuyi County]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u6b66\u4e49\u53bf}}\n| align=right| W\u01d4y\u00ec Xi\u00e0n\n|-\n| align=left | [[Pujiang County, Zhejiang|Pujiang County]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u6d66\u6c5f\u53bf}}\n| align=right| P\u01d4ji\u0101ng Xi\u00e0n\n|-\n| align=left | [[Pan'an County]]\n| align=middle | {{lang|zh-Hans|\u78d0\u5b89\u53bf}}\n| align=right| P\u00e1n'\u0101n Xi\u00e0n\n|}\n\nThese are further divided into 191 [[Administrative divisions of the People's Republic of China#Township level|township-level divisions]], including 107 [[town of China|towns]], 73 [[Township (People's Republic of China)|townships]] and 11 [[subdistrict]]s.\n\n==Economy==\nJinhua has a rather flexible economic system with distinctive economic characteristics in different areas.  90% of enterprises are in and about 88% of its [[Gross domestic product|GDP]] are from private sector.{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n\n===Industry===\n[[File:JNP6120G.jpg|thumb|A bus made by the local [[Jinhua Youngman Vehicle]] factory.]]\nJinhua enjoys an advanced civilian-owned economy, with its industry mainly supported by processing and manufacturing. Leading industries of the city include [[clothing]] and [[Textile industry|textile]], [[Mechanical engineering|mechanics]] and [[electronics]], [[Pharmaceutical industry|pharmacy]] and [[Chemical industry|chemistry]], [[Craft production|manufacturing crafts]], [[Metalworking|metalwork]] processing architecture and [[building material]]s, [[automobile]]-and-[[motorcycle accessories]], [[food processing]], and plastic ware.{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n\nIndustries are distributed with different characteristics in different counties or county-level cities. For instance, [[Yiwu]] is characterized by its [[Light industry|light-industry]] commodities, [[Yongkang, Zhejiang|Yongkang]] by its [[automobile]]-and-[[motorcycle accessories]] and mechanical and electric tools, [[Dongyang]] by its [[clothing]], architecture and [[Magnet|magnetic materials]], the Jinhua Proper by its pharmacy, construction materials and industrial measures, [[Lanxi, Zhejiang|Lanxi]] by its non-ferrous [[metal]], [[cement]], [[towel]]s and daily chemicals, and [[Pujiang County, Zhejiang|Pujiang]] by its [[Textile industry|textile]], lockmaking, and lantern ornaments of [[crystal]]s.{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n\n====Handicrafts====\nTraditional [[handicraft]]s have been flourishing in Jinhua. The [[wood carving]] and [[bamboo]] weaving in [[Dongyang]], the [[straw plaiting]], lace purling and [[crystal]]s carving in [[Pujiang County, Zhejiang|Pujiang]], and the hardware crafts in [[Yongkang, Zhejiang|Yongkang]], all enjoy a long history of development and the products sell well both abroad and at home.{{citation needed|date=July 2016}}\n\n==Transportation==\n[[File:201812 New Jinhua Railway Station.jpg|thumb|[[Jinhua Railway Station]]]]\nMain Railway station: \n[[Jinhua Railway Station]]\n[[Jinhua South Railway Station]]\n[[Yiwu Railway Station]]\n\nJinhua enjoys convenient transportation, being the communications center in southeast China between coastal and inland areas. It is one of the major hubs of landway transportation in the country. The [[Zhejiang]]-[[Jiangxi]], Jinhua-[[Wenzhou]] and Jinhua-[[Qiandaohu]] railways intersect in the city. The [[Hangzhou]]-Jinhua-[[Quzhou]] Expressway, the Jinhua-[[Lishui, Zhejiang|Lishui]]-[[Wenzhou]] Expressway, the No. 330 and 320 National Highways, and other provincial highroads traverse the area. The city aggregation around Jinhua Proper has formed a \"Half-an-Hour's-Ride Economic Circle\", there being merely a 90-minute and a 3-hour journey driving from the city to [[Hangzhou]] and [[Shanghai]] respectively.\n\n[[Yiwu Airport]] offers airlines destined for [[Beijing]], [[Shanghai]], [[Guangzhou]], [[Shenzhen]], [[Xiamen]], [[Qingdao]], and [[Hong Kong]].\n\n== Landmarks ==\n[[Jinhua Architecture Park]], a collection of 17 pavilions designed by Chinese and international architects, set on the banks of the [[Yiwu River]].\n\nChina's Wuju opera theatre\uff0cmainly for opera, ballet, drama, concerts, variety show comprehensive cultural facilities, is one of the landmark building of jinhua city. It is located in Jinhua city east city south street, west of bing rainbow Jin Huajiang north of east road, yiwu, jiang Wu Yijiang sanjiang interchange Dovetail State Park area\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.jinhua.gov.cn Government website of Jinhua] {{in lang|zh}}\n*[http://english.jinhua.gov.cn Government website of Jinhua]{{in lang|en}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060803134933/http://community.middlebury.edu/~knutson/pictures/jinhua.html Jinhua First Social Welfare Institute] (orphanage)\n*[http://www.ansi.okstate.edu/breeds/swine/jinhua/ The Jinhua Swine], breeds of livestock\n\n{{Zhejiang topics}}\n{{Zhejiang}}\n{{Jinhua\u2013Wenzhou Railway}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Zhejiang]]\n[[Category:Jinhua| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses}}\n{{stack begin}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields that may be available-->\n<!--See the Table at Infobox settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|name                   = {{raise|0.2em|Jinhua}}\n|official_name          = \n|other_name             = Kinhwa, Tsin Ua \n|native_name            = {{lower|0.1em|{{nobold|{{lang|zh-hans|\u91d1\u534e\u5e02}}}}}}\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        =[[Prefecture-level city]]\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          = Jinhuamontage.jpg\n|imagesize              = 250px\n|image_caption          = Clockwise from top: Bridging Tea House in [[Jinhua Architecture Park]], [[Jinhua Railway Station]], Jinhua City 1, Jinhua City 2\n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              = \n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_type      =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              = {{maplink|frame=yes|plain=yes|type=shape|stroke-width=2|stroke-color=#000000|zoom=7}}\n|image_map1             = ChinaZhejiangJinhua.png\n|mapsize1               =  \n|map_caption1           = Location of Jinhua City jurisdiction in Zhejiang\n|image_dot_map          =\n|pushpin_map            = \n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_map_caption    =\n|p